File Information
Collection: Mantis Bug Tracker REST API
Environment: ambiente_mantis
Collection Description
Mantis Bug Tracker (MantisHub) REST APIs. REST API calls have to be authenticated by creating an API token for the user doing the calls, and then passing the API token in the &#39;Authorization&#39; header. However, for anonymous access, the API key and header are not needed. Postman Environment Variables: - {{token}} - The API token to be used for authentication. - {{url}} - The base URL for Mantis instance (e.g. &#39;https://instance-name.mantishub.io&#39;). There has been significant improvements and feature additions for REST API in each of the recent releases. Hence, it is highly recommended to use latest release when leveraging the REST APIs. REST API is enabled by default since MantisBT 2.8.0 release.

Test NameAssertion Error
Iteration: 1 - Monitor an issue (for specified users)
Request Description
Have one or more users monitor the specified issue. The users can be identified via: - id - their user id. - name - their username - email - their email address - name_or_realname - a string that corresponds to their username or real name. If user id is not specified, the logged in user id is added to the issue as the monitoring user. If user id is not the same as logged in user id, a high access level is required which enables adding other users to the monitor list. Available since MantisBT 2.11.0.

Iteration: 1 - Get Configuration Option
Request Description
Get specified config option. If an option doesn't exist or is marked as private, it will be silently skipped. Some config options get extra handling to provide more useful response. For example: - Enumerations - The enumeration is parsed into an array of objects, each object including id, name and localized label. For list of possible config options to retrieve see the following file: https://github.com/mantisbt/mantisbt/blob/master/config_defaults_inc.php When requesting an option, don't supply the `$g_` prefix for the string name. Only options that are listed as public can be retrieved via this API. Search the `config_defaults_inc.php` file for `$g_public_config_names` to see the list of public options. Available since MantisBT 2.3.0.

Iteration: 1 - Get Multiple Configuration Options
Request Description
Get specified config options. If an option doesn't exist or is marked as private, it will be silently skipped. Some config options get extra handling to provide more useful response. For example: - Enumerations - The enumeration is parsed into an array of objects, each object including id, name and localized label. For list of possible config options to retrieve see the following file: https://github.com/mantisbt/mantisbt/blob/master/config_defaults_inc.php When requesting an option, don't supply the `$g_` prefix for the string name. Only options that are listed as public can be retrieved via this API. Search the `config_defaults_inc.php` file for `$g_public_config_names` to see the list of public options. Available since MantisBT 2.3.0.
